<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="311" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,679,848]" pageId="16" pageNumber="311">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,751,776]" pageId="16" pageNumber="311">Comments</emphasis>
. Distributional records for this species from 
<collectingCountry box="[833,887,752,775]" name="Peru" pageId="16" pageNumber="311">Peru</collectingCountry>
, to which it seems to be endemic, were provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Polhemus, D. A." box="[188,422,788,813]" pageId="16" pageNumber="311" pagination="151 - 162" refId="ref11987" refString="Polhemus, D. A. (2014) Two new Peruvian species of Paravelia (Heteropera: Veliidae) from water-filled bamboo internodes, and distributional notes for other Paravelia species. Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 157, 151 - 162. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 22119434 - 00002043" type="journal article" year="2014">D. Polhemus (2014)</bibRefCitation>
. The male abdominal terminalia of this species have not been previously illustrated, and figures are provided here (
<figureCitation box="[447,598,823,848]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1569,1591]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,185,1551]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,185,1551]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 11. A Altavelia willei, male, dorsal view. B. Altavelia willei, male, dorsal view. C. Altavelia willei, male, apex of abdomen, lateral view. D. Altavelia willei, male, dorsal view, apex of abdomen (Figs. 11A, C and D, specimen from Peru, Dept. Ancash, as listed in D. Polhemus 2014)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2637362/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="311">Figs. 11 C, D</figureCitation>
) to aid in future recognition of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
